Hi Paige,

I&#39;ve been teaching my daughter, who is in first grade, to write her
spelling words in QS and she loves it! Examples from this week: &quot;pig&quot;
and &quot;kick&quot;. An example of a missed word from the week before: &quot;what&quot;
mispelled &quot;wut&quot;. (They&#39;re taught to sound out words.) My son is in
third grade and also loves it, but to him it&#39;s more of a secret code.
It&#39;s definitely more fun than practicing cursive, which he sees no
point in doing. My wife rolls her eyes and asks, Why don&#39;t you just
learn to spell?

I didn&#39;t really set out to teach them, but when I offered to sit down
and write with them on the same ruled paper they use at school, they
were all over it.

Ted


